{% extends "www/_layouts/layout-fullwidth.njk" %} 
{% set pageTitle="A to Z content style guide" %} {% set section = "Styles" %} 
{# Imports #} 
{%- from "wmnds/components/content-tiles/normal/_normal.njk" import wmndsContentTilesNormal -%}
{% from "wmnds/components/link/link/_link.njk" import wmndsLink %}
{% from "wmnds/components/inset-text/_inset-text.njk" import wmndsInsetText %} 
{# Set array of tiles #} 
{% block content %} 

{# About the style guide #}
<div class="wmnds-grid">
  <div class="wmnds-col-1 wmnds-col-md-3-4">
    <h2>Writing content for West Midlands Network</h2>
    <h3>User-focused content</h3>
    <p>
      You should create all content with user-focused content design principles. This means content has an identified
      user need and is written in plain English.
    </p>
    <p>
      Read the
      {{
        wmndsLink({
          link: 'https://www.gov.uk/guidance/content-design/what-is-content-design',
          linkTitle: 'GOV.UK introduction to content design',
          text: 'GOV.UK introduction to content design'
        })
      }}
      to find out more.
    </p>
    <p>Design Team can help you to test your content with user research.</p>
    <br />
    <h3>About the A-Z of style guide</h3>
    <p>This style guide will help you to use consistent words across West Midlands Network services.</p>
    <p>
      If something is not covered by this style guide, check the
      {{
        wmndsLink({
          link: 'https://www.gov.uk/guidance/style-guide/a-to-z-of-gov-uk-style',
          linkTitle: 'GOV.UK Style Guide',
          text: 'GOV.UK style guide'
        })
      }}
      .
    </p>
    <p>You can also email Samresha Purewal if you think something is missing from this guidance.</p>
    <p>
      {{ wmndsInsetText({ thinner: true, html: "If you’re talking about day-to-day services (bus, train or tram), you
      may need to make it clear that West Midlands Network does not run these.<br /><br />For example, you could say:
      \“We don’t run the buses, trains or trams. We can point you in the right direction if you need help.\"" }) }}
    </p>
    <br />
    <h3>A to Z of style</h3>
    <p>
      JSON data is in here, organised by letter in accordion. The user should have the option to expand all and collapse
      all.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<br />
{% endblock %}
